title: Gateway Tire & Service Criterium Race Series 2011
Tennessee State Individual Time Trial Championship
2011 Pedalfest
description: The ETSU Cycling Team has taken over the reigns of the \"Pedalfest\" held in Elizabethton, TN. The \"Pedalfest\" was started and organized by Hampton Trails bike shop some years ago, and has been very successful every year. It\'s a road ride that leaves Elizabethton City Park and takes you to the Watauga Dam where refreshments await the riders at the turn around. After leaving the dam you will have an option to take the route back to the city park or add a 10 mile loop giving you a 22 mile or 32 mile ride. This years event will kick off on Saturday May 28, 2010. Visit the registration page at www.etsycycling.org for more information about the ETSU Cycling Club & the event! All funds raised go to support the ETSU Cycling Team.
course: The red route denotes the 22 mile route, after leaving the dam riders will return to the city park.The green route denotes the longer route (33 miles) after departing the dam follow the green route above to add an extra 10 miles to the ride before returning to the city park.
directions:
START:

Ride begins at 9:30am at the city park and ball fields near the carter county jail. Its the parking lot where the Roan Groan organizes the start. Look for the farthest pavilion for check-in. Please come support the ETSU Cycling Team.

HUB Endurance Cross Clinic Series
description: HUB Endurance Cyclocross Practice Race Series
course: A developed cyclocross course, including grass fields, barrier carry\'s, run-ups, and dirt hills. Each event in the series will consist of: 1) Instruction and course description from a USAC coach. 2) Thirty minutes of warm-up laps. 3) Thirty minutes of optional fast paced, hot laps.
registration: On-site registration only. Daily registration fee is only $1 for USA Cycling members to cover insurance fees. Cost for non-USAC members is $6 to cover a one day non-competitive USAC license and insurance fees.
notes: This is a cyclocross practice race series only. There will be no awards, or prizes. Each week will feature technique instruction from certified USAC coaches, and a different course layout to prepare athletes for all variables that they could expect at cyclocross races.  Riders must wear helmets that meet the US DOT helmet standards, or the US Consumer Product Safety Commission approved helmets.  All bar ends must be removed if you are using a mountain bike.
directions: The series will be held at Pointe Property Group (1200 Premier Dr., Chattanooga, TN 37421), conveniently located off I-75 and East Brainerd Rd.
